                "style": "medium",
                "boxed": true
            },
            "content": "DelegateEvents delegates <span class='quote'>event listeners</span> to a single element, the root element of the app.  The utility can be applied to any DOM element, not only compoents. Depending on the <span class='quote'>current target</span>, the appropriate callback will be selected.<br/>  The module will execute only <span class='quote'>one event at a time</span>, waiting for the end of the application’s internal <span class='quote'>tick</span>."
        },
        {
            "component": "mob-spacer",
            "props": {
                "style": "small"
            }
        },
        {
            "component": "mob-paragraph",
            "props": {
                "style": "medium",
                "boxed": true,
                "note": true
            },
            "content": "Since the number of events is limited to <span class='quote'>one per tick</span>, it is possible that not all <span class='quote'>overlapping</span> events will be executed. An example could be using <span class='quote'>input</span> and <span class='quote'>change</span> events applied to the <span class='quote'>same element</span>.<br/> In these specific cases, it is advisable to use the browser’s native <span class='quote'>eventListener API</span> for more granular control. Specific workarounds for these cases have not been implemented to keep the code simpler and to allow reliance on native DOM events when needed."
        },
